				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm repeating a few questions, simply because they need to be answered.
<br />

<br />
1) What is the description of our class? We have allways been told that we are meant to be "respectable damage dealers" and have the best summoned pet, and if this is true why are the other 2 "pet" classes' pets 95% of ours? (ie, should most of our damage come from our nukes, or our pets?)
<br />

<br />
2) When will there be upgrades to our pet's damage, and how powerfull will the pets in OOW be? Just how much of an upgrade are we looking at?
<br />

<br />
3) Where will be we in the new expansion- will we be in the top DPS slots or will we continue to slide down the slippery slope of better melee weapons and immensly greater Wizards nukes (thus allowing them to gain more with focii)
<br />

<br />
4) Why is there such a gap in pet focii levels, currently we go from LDoN (Takish 650 points) to VT (where most Mages never see, even those beyond it in progression) to PoTime and beyond? No other classes have to endure that much of a gap in weapons. For instance Rogue daggers are all over from BoT to MM to SolRo. 
<br />

<br />
5) How about making the pets scale more dramatically with the focii, seeing as they are supposed to be half of our arsenal?
<br />

<br />
6)Why do Druids continue to match us in nuking power while pulling ahead with specific AA's like Quick Damage (and DC pets when available) especially while our pets are not adequate to fill the gap between Priest and DPS class?
<br />

<br />
7) Why are we the only DPS class without an aggro reducer when at the moment most of our damage comes from our nukes?
<br />

<br />
8) Will current Focus items scale to 70, and if so where will it start? (Eps, Time, GoD...)
<br />

<br />
9) How about some powerful Mage self pet only items? I'm sick of being a vending machine, especially when doing so closes the gaps between other classes and Mages.<br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: red">
<br />
Fear can sometimes be a useful emotion. For instance, let's say you're an astronaught on the moon and you fear that your partner has been turned into Dracula. The next time he goes out for the moon pieces, wham!, you just slam the door behind him and blast off. He might call you on the radio and say he's not Dracula, but you just say, "Think again, bat man."
<br />
- Jack Handy</span></span>
